<quantity box="[1177,1267,1945,1973]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.96" pageId="18" pageNumber="171" unit="km" value="296.0">296 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[636,786,1981,2007]" pageId="18" pageNumber="171" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found in the conservation units “Refúgio da Vida Silvestre de Amargosa” and “Estação Ecológica Estadual Wenceslau Guimarães”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="172" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[136,1452,158,401]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,158,184]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,551,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis box="[294,551,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Bertolonia linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[731,799,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane forest (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1257,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers in January and November, fruits in January, August, October and November. The species is easily distinguished from other species of the genus mainly because of its lanceolate, 
<quantity box="[1283,1388,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" unit="cm" value="1.25" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2 cm</quantity>
wide leaf blades, but also by the rounded or attenuate leaf base and acute apex. Only two other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raddi" authorityYear="1820" box="[1271,1391,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1391,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Bertolonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar leaf blades: 
<taxonomicName authority="Cogniaux (1886: 56)" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityPageNumber="56" authorityYear="1886" box="[357,764,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[357,523,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">B. angustifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cogniaux, A." box="[530,764,302,329]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" refId="ref19057" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1886) Bertolonia (Melastomataceae). In: Martius, C. F. P., Eichler, A. G. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis. Vol. 14. Lipsiae Frid. Fleischer, Monachii. pp. 49 - 57." type="book" year="1886">Cogniaux (1886: 56)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Baumgratz (1990: 141)" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityPageNumber="141" authorityYear="1990" box="[819,1244,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valenteana">
<emphasis box="[819,974,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">B. valenteana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[981,1244,302,329]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz (1990: 141)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both occurring in 
<collectingRegion box="[136,366,338,365]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Rio de Janeiro state</collectingRegion>
. Moreover, it has flowers with pink petals and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[330,539,374,401]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[401,450,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[593,677,374,400]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
